article_title: Andreessen Horowitz Makes First Major Digital Health Investment With Omada Health

article_metadata.description: Omada Health, which is pioneering the application of clinically validated programs online, raised $23 million in a series B round. Andreessen Horowitz led the investment, with participation from Kaiser Permanente Ventures, and returning investors U.S. Venture Partners and the Vertical Group—bringing the total amount raised to $28.4 million.
